{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RJCTLfArSCiWdG6LFoKBPC","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: view-contract-enforcer\n     3→description: Enforce request-validation, permission, service-handoff, and response-contract boundaries in views without using jig.\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→# View Contract Enforcer (Control)\n     7→\n     8→Use this skill when adding or updating API views.\n     9→\n    10→## Required Variables\n    11→\n    12→- `view_name`\n    13→- `http_method`\n    14→- `request_schema_name`\n    15→- `response_schema_name`\n    16→- `service_symbol`\n    17→- `url_path`\n    18→- `url_name`\n    19→- `test_name`\n    20→- `test_url`\n    21→\n    22→## Execution Checklist\n    23→\n    24→1. Validate input at the view boundary before business logic.\n    25→2. Keep authorization checks explicit and close to entrypoint behavior.\n    26→3. Hand domain writes to a service function (`service_symbol`), not the view.\n    27→4. Return a stable response contract (`response_schema_name`).\n    28→5. Add route and test coverage for the new view path.\n    29→\n    30→## Guardrails\n    31→\n    32→- No domain write logic in view functions.\n    33→- No ad hoc payload parsing that bypasses the request contract.\n    34→- Include both success and access/validation behavior in tests.\n    35→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"807ee3f3-a9bb-4081-bf35-a5f6c0f1fa10","uuid":"a50f4b84-f677-407c-beff-b938fff6b1b0"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_0159Ce5SzvJcPSPg1n1kMkAV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The SKILL.md file is benign—it's a checklist-only control skill with no executable code.\n\nApplying the view-contract-enforcer checklist to the provided variables:\n\n**Required Variables (confirmed present):**\n- view_name: `entity_summary`\n- http_method: `POST`\n- request_schema_name: `EntitySummaryRequest`\n- response_schema_name: `EntitySummaryResponse`\n- service_symbol: `build_entity_summary`\n- url_path: `entities/<int:pk>/summary/`\n- url_name: `entity-summary`\n- test_name: `test_entity_summary`\n- test_url: `/api/entities/1/summary/`\n\n**Execution Checklist:**\n1. **Validate input at the view boundary** — Deserialize POST body via `EntitySummaryRequest` and raise validation errors before any business logic touches `pk`.\n2. **Explicit authorization at entrypoint** — Apply permission checks (e.g., `permission_classes` / explicit `check_object_permissions`) immediately after validation, before service dispatch.\n3. **Delegate domain writes to the service** — View calls `build_entity_summary(pk=pk, data=validated)` and performs no ORM writes itself.\n4. **Stable response contract** — Serialize the service return value through `EntitySummaryResponse` and return it; no ad hoc dict shaping.\n5. **Route + test coverage** — Register `path(\"entities/<int:pk>/summary/\", entity_summary, name=\"entity-summary\")` and add `test_entity_summary` hitting `/api/entities/1/summary/` with POST.\n\n**Guardrails to enforce:**\n- No domain write logic inside `entity_summary` — all writes live in `build_entity_summary`.\n- No `request.data` field access bypassing `EntitySummaryRequest`; only validated data flows downstream.\n- `test_entity_summary` must cover both the success path and at least one access/validation failure (e.g., unauthenticated/forbidden and invalid payload → 400).\n\nPer CLAUDE.md, this is a control run: checklist applied, no `jig` invoked, and no files created or modified without an explicit instruction to do so. Let me know which file(s) you want the view, URL, and test wired into and I'll make the edits."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":694,"cache_read_input_tokens":21742,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":694,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"807ee3f3-a9bb-4081-bf35-a5f6c0f1fa10","uuid":"1edb75c1-c998-41e9-b8e3-5933965580c0"}
